The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | TCS bags Volkswagen deal
                                                                                                               TCS bags Volkswagen deal
          A STAFF REPORTER                                            
	Calcutta, May 13: Tata Consultancy Services  the countrys No. 1 software exporter  has clinched a five-year deal to provide IT transformation and support services to automobile manufacturer Volkswagen Groups operations in the UK.        
	The company today informed the bourses about the contract without revealing any financial details.        
	TCS said it would leverage its global network delivery model to provide onshore and offshore support and transformation services for Volkswagens operations in the UK, and across brands that include Audi, SEAT, Skoda, Volkswagen passenger cars and commercial vehicles.         
	The Indian company will support Volkswagen in its business transformation programme to meet its aim to sell more cars, sell more parts and drive down costs.        
	TCS will support all brands within the group as they move to a consolidated, standardised business platform, by providing geographic mobility, increased flexibility and lower costs. This is the first time Volkswagen has implemented an onshore-offshore model for its IT systems.         
	In this challenging environment, organisations are looking to increase efficiency and flexibility to stay competitive, said A.S. Lakshminarayanan, vice-president and head of Europe, TCS.         
	In the current economic climate, ensuring a business is fit, well and lean, in this way, is the key to success, he said.        
	Shares of TCS today closed at Rs 622.45 on the Bombay Stock Exchange, down 15.05 per cent from the previous days close of Rs 637.50.                                                                                                                                        
